SPARK-SQL

createOrReplaceTempView
======================
    1. It is used for create distributed table from spark daaframe.
    2. After creating table we can perform all  the operation by writing sql query.
        Ex. 
            data = [(1, "Alice", 25), (2, "Bob", 30)]
            columns = ["id", "name", "age"]
            df = spark.createDataFrame(data, columns)

            # Create a temporary view
            df.createOrReplaceTempView("people")

            # Query using Spark SQL
            spark.sql("SELECT * FROM people WHERE age > 25").show()
 
    3. If we want it accessible across multiple SparkSessions within the same app.
        df.createOrReplaceGlobalTempView("people")
        spark.sql("SELECT * FROM global_temp.people").show()

        # First SparkSession
        spark = SparkSession.builder.appName("App1").getOrCreate()
        df.createOrReplaceGlobalTempView("people")

        # Another SparkSession within the same application
        spark2 = spark.newSession()
        spark2.sql("SELECT * FROM global_temp.people").show()

