Join in dataframe.

`.join keyword is used for joining the dataframe`

.join - It will take 3 parameter.
    leftDf.join(rightDf,condition,typeOfJoin)
    
    condition = on which colume we have join two df


Types of joins
    1. inner
        df1.join(df2, df1.id == df2.id, "inner").select(col("id"))  --> id column is ambigus

    2. left/left_outer
        df1.join(df2, df1.id == df2.id, "left")

    3. right/right_outer
        df1.join(df2, df1.id == df2.id, "right")

    4. Full Join
        df1.join(df2, df1.id == df2.id, "full")

    5. Left Semi Join ( does not include columns from the right DataFrame )
        df1.join(df2, df1.id == df2.id, "left_semi")

    6. Left Anti Join
        df1.join(df2, df1.id == df2.id, "left_anti")

    7. cross join
        df1.crossJoin(df2)


